casebody.data:
Wednesday, March 25, 1998

MERIT DOCKET

98-89. State ex rel. Orth v. Christiansen.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus. Upon consideration of respondent’s motion to dismiss,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the motion to dismiss be, and hereby is, granted.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
